{
  "stem": "268.4",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Because the director of the factory kept telling the authorities that we are-- we are so dearly needed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They gave us special pass.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We could go outside the ghetto in formation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "We always marched in formation.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You never-- you never went by yourself.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And 40 people or 45-- whoever was missing-- you know, you'd be written up.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But we'd come back the same amount.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And we would come with these papers and, of course, then we could leave the ghetto and come back.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that enabled us to do, at least, postpone-- to stave off-- the deportation until the moments for another-- until 1943, which is almost four years into-- yeah, well, four years into the war.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And not being deported.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Even though most of the ghetto was already empty.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But this guy saved us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "This one particular place, where, as in Warsaw ghetto, was like Umshlagplatz, this one was a place of assembly.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "The Germans would-- they would know how to hurt the Jewish people, not only physically, but mentally, as well.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "For instance, they would-- the biggest raid was always on high holidays or Jewish holidays of Passover or Shavuot or Sukkot.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "They would also take institutions such as a Jewish orphanage-- which was a pre-war orphanage in this one town of [NON-ENGLISH], which was the adjoining town-- the next big ghetto.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they would make the place of assembly for deportation.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This is where they would bring people in and separate women, children, sick, old, young.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And from there, they would ship to Auschwitz, to deportation, to death camps, of course.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And some to work camps.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But the sierociniec-- that's a Polish name.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "Sierociniec means orphanage.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The orphanage was the assembly place.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
